disableWhitelist().notice: Removes the whitelist requirement for minting.

mintStatus().notice: True/False value indicating whether minting is enabled.

mintingFee().notice: The fee to mint each token in this collection.

publicMaxMints().notice: The maximum tokens that are allowed to be minted during  a single publicMint transaction.

publicMint(uint256).notice: Mint function for use with public minting sales. Mint Fees in native token,  requires amount * mintPrice to be sent by caller.

release().notice: Releases funds from the contract to the addresses owed payment.  Only the owner can call this function.

setBaseURI(string).notice: Updates the base URI for the token metadata  it does not emit an event so that it can be set invisibly to purchasers  and avoid token sniping.

setMaxPublicMints(uint256).notice: Sets the maximum number of tokens a single address can mint AT A TIME  during the public mint period. Keep in mind that regardless of the number set, during public  minting any user will still be able to call the publicMint function an unlimited number of times

setMaxWhitelistMints(uint64).notice: Sets the maximum number of tokens a whitelisted user can mint.

setMintPrice(uint256).notice: this will set the fees required to mint using  publicMint(), must enter in wei. So 1 ETH = 10**18.

setMintSize(uint256).notice: Sets the mint size. Cannot be smaller than the totalSupply().

setRoyaltyInfo(address,uint256).notice: Sets single address EIP-2981 royalty information for this collection.

setWhitelistMerkleRoot(bytes32).notice: Sets a new Merkle root used to verify whitelist membership  in combination with a proof submitted to the whitelistMint function.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the metadata URI for a given token.

whitelistMaxMints().notice: The maximum tokens that are allowed to be minted   by a whitelisted address.

whitelistMint(bytes32[],uint64).notice: Mint function for use with whitelist minting sales. Mint fees in native token,  requires amount * mintPrice to be sent by caller.

whitelistStatus().notice: True/False value indicating that the whitelist is currenly required for minting.
